  "text": "Once upon a matchday — it was the round of 16, on the 7th of July 2026 — two teams walked out under the soft evening lights. Argentina produced a stunning comeback, turning a two-goal deficit into a stoppage-time victory. The reigning champions stared elimination in the face, two goals down and with their talisman's penalty already saved.\n\nFirst, in the 46th minute, Omar Ibrahim made it 0–1; then, in the 67th minute, Zico made it 0–2; then, in the 79th minute, Cristian Romero made it 1–2; then, in the 84th minute, Lionel Messi made it 2–2; and at last, in the 94th minute, Enzo Fernández made it 3–2.\n\nOmar Ibrahim and Zico had Egypt dreaming at 2-0, and Lionel Messi even saw a penalty saved by an inspired Mohamed Shobeir. Then the tie turned on its head: Cristian Romero powered in a header from Messi's cross, before Messi himself pounced on a loose ball for his 21st career World Cup goal. In the second minute of stoppage time, Enzo Fernández arrived with a lung-busting run to head Lautaro Martínez's cross into the top corner. Champions find a way, and Argentina — through sheer force of Messi's will — found one when it mattered most.\n\nAnd so the story ended Argentina 3–2 Egypt. Argentina carried on their long journey, and Egypt lay down to rest. Every goal in this tale is a true one — kept safe and provable on the blockchain by TxLINE — so you can close your eyes knowing not a single fact was ever made up. Sleep well, and goodnight.",
